# Multi-Switch Network Segmentation and VLAN Routing Lab

## Overview

This lab was created in Cisco Packet Tracer to practice VLAN segmentation, trunking, and inter-VLAN routing in a multi-switch environment.

The network consists of:
- 1 Router
- 2 Switches
- 5 PCs
- 3 VLANs/Subnets

The objective of this lab was to configure communication between VLANs using router-on-a-stick while maintaining proper VLAN segmentation across multiple switches.

---

# Network Topology

## Devices Used
- 1 Cisco Router
- 2 Cisco 2960 Switches
- 5 PCs

## VLANs and Subnets

| VLAN | Name | Subnet |
|------|------|------|
| 10 | SALES | 192.168.10.0/24 |
| 20 | IT | 192.168.20.0/24 |
| 30 | HR | 192.168.30.0/24 |

---

# Technologies Used

- Cisco Packet Tracer
- VLAN Configuration
- 802.1Q Trunking
- Inter-VLAN Routing
- Router-on-a-Stick
- Access Ports
- Trunk Ports
- Layer 2 Switching
- Layer 3 Routing
- CLI Troubleshooting

---

# Objectives

- Create multiple VLANs
- Assign switch ports to VLANs
- Configure trunk links between switches
- Configure router-on-a-stick inter-VLAN routing
- Verify communication between VLANs
- Troubleshoot VLAN and trunking issues

---

# Router Configuration Example

interface g0/0.10
 encapsulation dot1Q 10
 ip address 192.168.10.1 255.255.255.0

interface g0/0.20
 encapsulation dot1Q 20
 ip address 192.168.20.1 255.255.255.0

interface g0/0.30
 encapsulation dot1Q 30
 ip address 192.168.30.1 255.255.255.0



# Switch Configuration Example

## Access Port Example


interface fa0/1
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 10


## Trunk Port Example

interface fa0/24
 switchport mode trunk




# Verification Commands

## Verify VLANs


show vlan brief


## Verify Trunks


show interfaces trunk


## Verify Router Interfaces


show ip interface brief




# Troubleshooting

During this lab several networking issues were encountered and resolved.

## Issues Encountered

- Native VLAN mismatch
- Incorrect trunk/access port assignments
- PCs unable to reach default gateway
- VLAN communication failures

## Troubleshooting Steps

- Verified VLAN assignments using `show vlan brief`
- Verified trunk ports using `show interfaces trunk`
- Reconfigured incorrectly assigned uplink ports
- Verified router subinterfaces and encapsulation
- Confirmed proper default gateway configuration on PCs

